WEBVTT

00:02.670 --> 00:04.467
- I thought it might be
the Chesapeake Ripper, but there

00:04.500 --> 00:07.037
were no surgical trophies taken.
I'm gonna need you to prepare

00:07.070 --> 00:09.368
yourself on this one.
- I'm prepared.

00:09.410 --> 00:12.072
- Yeah, prepare yourself some
more. It's soup in there.
- Jack gave you his word

00:12.110 --> 00:15.432
he would protect your headspace,
yet he leaves you to your
mental devices.

00:15.480 --> 00:18.040
- Are you trying to alienate me
from Jack Crawford?

00:18.080 --> 00:21.243
- It's difficult to lie still
and fear gomg to sleep when
it's there to think about.

00:21.280 --> 00:24.317
(siren)
- Do you have a history
of sleepwalking, Mr. Graham?

00:24.350 --> 00:26.818
- My wife and I need to talk.
May we use your waiting room?

00:26.860 --> 00:29.488
- Lung cancer.
- When were you gonna tell me?

00:29.530 --> 00:32.294
- Do I seem different?
- But you've always been
a little different.

00:32.330 --> 00:34.457
- It's getting harder and harder
to make myself look.

00:34.500 --> 00:36.525
- I'm not gonna tell you
what you ought to do.

00:36.570 --> 00:39.164
- I don't know how much longer
I can be all that useful
to you, Jack.

00:39.200 --> 00:41.293
- Really? The last three we had,
you caught.

00:41.340 --> 00:43.399
- You can't arrest_ me
for writing an article.

00:43.440 --> 00:46.409
- You don't write another word
about Will Graham and
I won't have to.

00:59.490 --> 01:01.685
- This is your final opportunity
to comply.

01:01.720 --> 01:04.780
On your feet, Dr. Gideon,
or we will restrain you.

01:08.200 --> 01:12.136
(door buzzer)

01:12.170 --> 01:15.094
Alright, lace your fingers
behind your head!

01:25.250 --> 01:27.514
Get a gurney!

01:57.350 --> 02:00.319
(monitor beeping)

02:09.660 --> 02:12.299
(flatline tone)

02:26.380 --> 02:28.735
- Well, thanks
to Freddie Lounds,

02:28.780 --> 02:30.748
there's an unconfirmed story
floating out there

02:30.780 --> 02:32.748
that the Chesapeake Ripper's
already in custody.

02:32.780 --> 02:34.748
- Unconfirmed.
Am I confirming?

02:34.780 --> 02:36.884
Fact-checking
for Freddie Lounds...

02:36.920 --> 02:39.218
- You're fact-checking
for me.

02:39.260 --> 02:41.353
- I always feel a little nervous
going into these places.

02:41.390 --> 02:42.857
- Why's that?

02:42.890 --> 02:44.858
- Afraid they won't let me out.
- Don't worry.

02:44.890 --> 02:46.858
I won't leave you here.
- Yeah, not today.

02:46.900 --> 02:49.869
- Dr. Bloom just called me
about you,

02:49.900 --> 02:52.789
Mr. Graham--or should I call you
Dr. Graham?

02:52.840 --> 02:54.865
- I'm not a doctor.
- You're not FBI either.

02:54.900 --> 02:56.868
That's a temporary
identification.

02:56.910 --> 02:58.866
- Mr. Graham teaches
at the academy.

02:58.910 --> 03:02.209
- Ah, a teacher. Please,
gentlemen, take a seat.

03:02.250 --> 03:03.649
- Thank you.

03:06.620 --> 03:08.815
Dr. Chilton, we're going
to need to see

03:08.850 --> 03:11.944
the crime scene while it's
still relatively undisturbed.

03:11.990 --> 03:14.959
- I assure you, for something
so disturbing, it is quite
undisturbed.

03:14.990 --> 03:17.925
- Why was a nurse left alone
with a prisoner

03:17.960 --> 03:20.599
in a high-security
psychiatric hospital?

03:20.630 --> 03:22.860
- For the two years
since he was brought here,

03:22.900 --> 03:24.595
Gideon behaved perfectly

03:24.630 --> 03:25.995
and gave every appearance

03:26.030 --> 03:28.635
of cooperating with attempts
at therapy. As dictated

03:28.670 --> 03:33.369
by our present administrator,
security around him was
slightly... relaxed.

03:33.410 --> 03:35.878
I cannot help
feeling responsible

03:35.910 --> 03:39.573
myself for what happened.
He sat directly across from me

03:39.620 --> 03:41.713
and I had no idea
what he was hiding.

03:41.750 --> 03:44.947
And now one
of our staff is dead.
- I understand, Doctor.

03:44.990 --> 03:47.356
Mr. Graham's going to need
to see the crime scene

03:47.390 --> 03:49.483
with as much privacy
as you can provide.

03:49.530 --> 03:51.589
- Oh, yes, that thing you do.

03:51.630 --> 03:55.953
You're quite the topic
of conversation in, uh,
psychiatric circles, Mr. Graham.

03:56.000 --> 03:58.560
-Am I?

03:58.600 --> 04:01.034
- Uh, yes.
A unique cocktail

04:01.070 --> 04:05.632
of personality disorders
and neuroses that make you
a highly skilled profiler.

04:05.670 --> 04:08.707
- He's not here to be analyzed.
- Perhaps he should be.

04:08.740 --> 04:11.049
We are woefully short
of material

04:11.080 --> 04:13.469
on your sort of thing,
Mr. Graham.

04:13.520 --> 04:15.476
Would you mind speaking
to some of the staff?

04:15.520 --> 04:18.489
- Doctor.
- No, no, no. Not this trip.

04:18.520 --> 04:20.886
Maybe a special visit.
- Thank you, Dr. Chilton.

04:20.920 --> 04:23.582
I'd like to see
the crime scene now.

04:23.630 --> 04:25.621
- So, Gideon was restrained?

04:25.660 --> 04:27.628
- Handcuffed.
- Hm.

04:27.660 --> 04:29.764
- He concealed a fork tine
in the palm of his hand

04:29.800 --> 04:32.360
and used it to pick the lock.
- Where is he now?

04:32.400 --> 04:35.437
- In his cell.
You'll note

04:35.470 --> 04:37.859
the removal of organs
and the abdominal mutilations

04:37.910 --> 04:40.037
are all consistent
with the Chesapeake Ripper.

04:40.080 --> 04:42.469
- So is the brutalization
of the corpses, but that doesn't

04:42.510 --> 04:44.671
change the fact that
the Ripper is still out there.

04:44.710 --> 04:46.974
- Jack, what I'm about
to show you

04:47.020 --> 04:49.318
suggests othenNise.
(door buzzer)

04:51.620 --> 04:55.659
- Dr. Chilton consulted
on the case when we failed

04:55.690 --> 04:58.557
to catch the Ripper after
his last series of murders.

05:13.410 --> 05:15.071
- The reason you failed

05:15.110 --> 05:17.840
and kept failing to capture
the Chesapeake Ripper...

05:17.880 --> 05:20.542
was I already had him.

06:21.980 --> 06:25.507
(monitor beeping)

06:41.230 --> 06:43.824
(flatline tone)

07:03.690 --> 07:05.544
(nurse crying out)

08:12.660 --> 08:14.651
- Um...

08:17.830 --> 08:18.979
As far as we know,

08:19.030 --> 08:21.624
it's been over two years since
the Chesapeake Ripper killed?

08:21.660 --> 08:24.663
- That's correct.

08:26.670 --> 08:28.991
- When was Gideon admitted?

08:29.040 --> 08:31.031
- Almost two years ago.

08:36.680 --> 08:39.171
Lass, Miriam Regina.
Come in.

08:39.210 --> 08:41.872
- Morning, Agent Crawford.

08:41.920 --> 08:44.616
- Sorry to pull you out
of class. There's nothing wrong.

08:44.650 --> 08:46.754
Uh, no reason
to be nervous.

08:46.790 --> 08:49.054
- I'm not_ nervous.
Curious.

08:49.090 --> 08:50.887
- Your instructors tell me

08:50.930 --> 08:53.899
that you are in the top 10%?
- Top five, sir.

08:53.930 --> 08:56.899
- You're gonna have
to stop correcting me
if we're gonna get along, Lass.

08:56.930 --> 08:58.795
Take a seat.

08:58.830 --> 09:00.798
You wrote me

09:00.840 --> 09:03.308
a letter when you qualified
for the academy.

09:03.340 --> 09:06.730
- I wasn't sure you got it.
You never replied.

09:06.780 --> 09:10.045
- Never do. Odds are against any
trainee completing the program.

09:10.080 --> 09:13.675
But I'm glad to see
you're still here.

09:13.720 --> 09:16.177
In your letter, you said
you wanted to work for me

09:16.220 --> 09:18.188
in the Violent Criminal
Apprehen5ion Program.

09:18.220 --> 09:20.017
- Yes, sir.
- There might be an opportunity.

09:20.060 --> 09:22.119
I'm assuming
that you're familiar

09:22.160 --> 09:24.355
with the Chesapeake Ripper.
- Yes.

09:24.390 --> 09:28.121
- The Ripper's very hot
right now. Killed his last two
victims in six days. There'll be

09:28.160 --> 09:30.219
at least one more body
and then nothing for months.

09:30.270 --> 09:32.966
- They say
he's a true sociopath.

09:33.000 --> 09:34.695
- What do you say?

09:34.740 --> 09:37.937
- I say they don't know
what else to label him.

09:37.970 --> 09:39.938
He has some
of the characteristics

09:39.980 --> 09:43.939
of what they call a sociopath--
no remorse or guilt at all.

09:43.980 --> 09:45.948
He won't have any
of the other marks.

09:45.980 --> 09:47.345
He won't be a drifter.

09:47.380 --> 09:49.780
He'll have no history
of trouble with the law.

09:49.820 --> 09:51.788
He'll be hard to catch.

09:51.820 --> 09:54.618
- I'm assigning you to the
Chesapeake Ripper task force.

09:54.660 --> 09:56.651
You're gonna work
directly under me.

09:58.660 --> 10:00.821
- I'm grateful for
the opportunity, Agent Crawford.

10:00.860 --> 10:04.091
But I can't help
wondering... why me?

10:04.130 --> 10:06.837
- You have _
a foren5ics fellowship,

10:06.870 --> 10:08.838
six years of law enforcement,

10:08.870 --> 10:12.772
a degree in psychology,
doctorate in criminology.

10:12.810 --> 10:16.974
And what I don't have are
enough warm bodies.

10:17.010 --> 10:20.309
So, I'm gonna need
your full attention on this.

10:20.350 --> 10:22.944
- (Miriam): Yes, sir.

10:24.950 --> 10:27.953
- Th_e_volume of Abel Gideon's
mail is becoming a nUIsance.

10:27.990 --> 10:31.949
Sometimes I feel
like his secretary
rather than his keeper.

10:31.990 --> 10:35.391
- Any specific correspondences
that stood out from the others?

10:35.430 --> 10:38.263
- Mostly researchers
or PhD candidates

10:38.300 --> 10:41.736
requesting interviews.
A scattered dozen lonely hearts

10:41.770 --> 10:45.035
seeking his hand in marriage.
- He butchered

10:45.070 --> 10:48.107
his last wife and her family
on Thanksgiving.

10:48.140 --> 10:51.143
- There's no accounting
for taste--or intelligence.

10:51.180 --> 10:55.139
- Murdering his wife was
impulsive. The Chesapeake Ripper

10:55.180 --> 10:57.944
is methodical, meticulous.

10:57.990 --> 10:59.981
That's why he's so hard
to catch.

11:00.020 --> 11:02.409
- Was so hard to catch.

11:05.060 --> 11:06.857
Will you be conducting
a joint interview?

11:06.900 --> 11:09.425
- Separate.
Compare and contrast.

11:09.460 --> 11:11.325
- I know you're anxious
to get on with it.

11:11.370 --> 11:14.237
You have talked to Gideon
before, for some length of time.

11:14.270 --> 11:16.909
- Well, I saw him mainly
in court. I wrote an article

11:16.940 --> 11:19.204
about him in the Journal
of Criminal Psychology.

11:19.240 --> 11:21.936
- He is very familiar
with you.

11:21.980 --> 11:24.403
He has given you
a lot of thought.

11:24.450 --> 11:27.010
- You had some sessions
with him?

11:27.050 --> 11:30.781
- Yes, two, a couple years
ago when he was first
institutionalized.

11:30.820 --> 11:34.312
- I've read your notes,
of course. They were
more or less helpful

11:34.360 --> 11:37.989
as I conducted my own interviews
with Dr. Gideon over the years.

11:38.030 --> 11:42.148
- Well, I'm glad I was helpful.
- (Will): More or less.

11:44.400 --> 11:46.288
- I'll go first.

11:46.330 --> 11:48.332
(door buzzer)

12:10.290 --> 12:13.748
- Why, Dr. Bloom.

12:13.800 --> 12:15.756
How wonderful to see you again.

12:15.800 --> 12:18.462
- You remembered.
- I've met a lot

12:18.500 --> 12:20.968
of psychiatrists in the last
two years. It's hard to forget

12:21.000 --> 12:23.059
one so sublime.

12:23.110 --> 12:25.908
- Thank you for your time,
Dr. Gideon. I won't waste it.

12:25.940 --> 12:27.908
Shall we begin?

12:27.940 --> 12:30.170
- Dr. Bloom,
what is this to be?

12:30.210 --> 12:32.974
I was caught red-handed.
I mean, literally.

12:33.020 --> 12:36.979
There's no mystery
as to whodunit. I did it.

12:37.020 --> 12:41.081
- The mystery is whether you are
who you say you are.

12:41.120 --> 12:43.486
Or not.
- Never liked being called

12:43.530 --> 12:45.555
the Chesapeake Ripper.

12:45.590 --> 12:49.253
Maybe something
with a little more wit.

12:49.300 --> 12:52.963
- Is that why you didn't take
credit for the Ripper murders
before now?

12:53.000 --> 12:56.959
- Just watching the goose chase
from the box seats.

12:57.010 --> 12:59.228
- Two years of goose chasing.

12:59.270 --> 13:02.330
You must be a very patient man.
- Are you just gonna run

13:02.380 --> 13:05.508
the psychopathic checklist here?
I have had my personality

13:05.550 --> 13:08.542
inventoried by the Minnesota
Multiphasic.

13:08.580 --> 13:10.980
- Would you prefer
a Rorschach test?

13:11.020 --> 13:13.113
- Well, if you're gonna
show me those pictures,

13:13.160 --> 13:16.982
maybe you should put a blood
pressure cuff to my genitals.

13:17.030 --> 13:21.057
I find it gives
a much truer gauge of reaction.

13:21.100 --> 13:24.866
- What effect were you hoping
to have by killing

13:24.900 --> 13:26.527
the night nurse?

13:26.570 --> 13:32.133
- The effect I was hoping
to have was her death.

13:32.170 --> 13:34.331
Mission accomplished.

13:34.380 --> 13:37.838
- Brutalization of the body was
done posthumously.

13:37.880 --> 13:39.939
- Chesapeake Ripper usually

13:39.980 --> 13:41.948
does that sort of thing during,

13:41.980 --> 13:43.948
not after.

13:43.990 --> 13:50.054
- I do not have to convince you
that I am the Chesapeake Ripper.

13:52.260 --> 13:54.820
- Seems that's what you need
to do.

13:58.130 --> 14:00.269
- Certainly what somebody needs.

14:12.210 --> 14:13.575
- Jack.

14:13.620 --> 14:15.417
Come in.

14:23.630 --> 14:25.552
- I'm sorry. Um...

14:27.560 --> 14:29.653
I was just, uh...

14:29.700 --> 14:31.668
- In the neighborhood.

14:31.700 --> 14:34.032
- Yeah, something
like that.

14:38.310 --> 14:40.278
- How's Mrs. Crawford?

14:40.310 --> 14:42.528
- Yeah, that's why I was
in the neighborhood.

14:44.550 --> 14:46.245
She's fine.

14:46.280 --> 14:48.373
Well, she tells me
that she's fine

14:48.420 --> 14:51.981
and she tells me
when she's not.

14:52.020 --> 14:54.318
- You expect me
to tell you more?

14:54.360 --> 14:57.523
- Look, Bella's
at a NATO conference.

14:57.560 --> 15:00.495
I can't talk to her.
She's working.

15:00.530 --> 15:04.068
I doubt I could talk
to her if she was here.
- About her condition?

15:04.100 --> 15:06.068
- Yeah. About her cancer,
about her dying.

15:06.100 --> 15:08.091
She doesn't want to talk
to me about it.

15:10.110 --> 15:13.204
- I am prohibited from talking
about it--doctor-patient
confidentiality.

15:13.240 --> 15:16.277
- You talk to me
about Will Graham.

15:16.310 --> 15:20.019
- Will Graham is_ not
offICIally my patient.
We have conversations.

15:20.050 --> 15:23.144
- What do you
consider this?

15:23.190 --> 15:24.782
- Desperate coping.

15:29.060 --> 15:32.689
- You don't think I have a right
to know what's happening
with my wife?

15:32.730 --> 15:36.427
- You have every right to know
what's happening,
but not from me.

15:36.460 --> 15:40.692
- Well, I'm not just gonna
stand outside my marriage
and watch this happen.

15:40.740 --> 15:42.662
If that's what she wants,
too bad.

15:42.700 --> 15:44.258
She married the wrong guy
for that.

15:46.270 --> 15:47.976
- I'll offer one insight.

15:48.010 --> 15:50.046
She doesn't think
she married the wrong guy.

15:55.280 --> 15:58.113
- I can't stop thinking about
when my wife is gonna die.

15:58.150 --> 16:01.051
I look at her side of the bed
and I think,

16:01.090 --> 16:03.081
"Is she gonna die there?"

16:05.090 --> 16:08.093
I can't stop thinking about it,
you understand? I can't stop.

16:10.500 --> 16:12.525
- You're dreading the loss
of your wife.

16:14.540 --> 16:16.132
- Yes.

16:22.610 --> 16:24.601
And I'm thinking
about other losses too.

16:27.320 --> 16:30.187
- What other losses are
you dreading?

16:33.720 --> 16:36.280
Jack, you can't save her.

16:36.320 --> 16:38.288
She won't let you.

16:38.330 --> 16:40.321
The cancer won't let you.

16:43.530 --> 16:45.794
Who else couldn't
you save?

16:45.830 --> 16:48.594
- (Miriam): Where is everyone?

16:48.640 --> 16:51.029
- It's just you and me
for the time being.

16:51.070 --> 16:54.278
Take a look around here.
Tell me what you see.

17:11.260 --> 17:14.388
- He did it all here.

17:14.430 --> 17:17.365
Did it while he was alive.
He struck the throat

17:17.400 --> 17:19.368
so he couldn't call for help.
- Do you think

17:19.400 --> 17:22.267
he was unconscious
when the Ripper did the ripping?

17:22.300 --> 17:24.302
- No, he'd want him awake.

17:26.570 --> 17:29.130
Organs were removed.

17:29.180 --> 17:32.479
Not all of them. He was choosy.
He took the liver, thymus,

17:32.510 --> 17:34.512
but left the heart.

17:37.320 --> 17:40.153
- What's he doing
with the organs?

17:40.190 --> 17:42.488
- Surgical trophies.

17:42.520 --> 17:45.751
He's a medical doctor, isn't he?
Is that why you call him
the Ripper?

17:45.790 --> 17:48.554
- Why do you say that?

17:50.570 --> 17:53.198
- Psychopaths are attracted
to surgical fields.

17:53.240 --> 17:56.562
They offer power.
They require the ability

17:56.600 --> 17:59.569
to make objective clinical
decisions without feeling.

17:59.610 --> 18:01.578
- White male?

18:01.610 --> 18:04.170
Forties? Fifties?

18:04.210 --> 18:07.441
- I don't know
that he's white.

18:07.480 --> 18:09.744
He's exotic somehow,

18:09.780 --> 18:12.340
which is why
you're gonna catch him.

18:12.390 --> 18:15.450
- I'm gonna catch him?

18:15.490 --> 18:18.584
- We call you the guru.

18:18.630 --> 18:21.224
You have a peculiar
cleverness.

18:21.260 --> 18:24.525
- I'll take _that
as a compliment.

18:24.570 --> 18:26.663
- You should.

18:26.700 --> 18:29.828
You'll probably spot him
before anybody else.

18:29.870 --> 18:32.304
- Or you will.

18:36.310 --> 18:39.700
Now I want you
to take a look at this.

18:43.420 --> 18:46.639
- There's no
detectable consistency
with the Ripper victims.

18:46.690 --> 18:48.908
He doesn't hunt exclusively
within his own ethnic group.

18:48.960 --> 18:51.520
He's killed all creeds,
colors, men and women.

18:51.560 --> 18:54.927
- She has the exact same
wound pattern as the last-known
victim of the Chesapeake Ripper.

18:54.960 --> 18:59.522
I mean exact.
- We never found a body
for his last-known victim.

18:59.570 --> 19:03.199
- Then the victim before that.

19:03.240 --> 19:06.300
- I see the Ripper,
but I don't...

19:06.340 --> 19:08.308
feel the Ripper.

19:08.340 --> 19:10.672
This is plagiarism.
- We never made

19:10.710 --> 19:13.941
the wound patterns for any
of the Ripper's victims public.

19:13.980 --> 19:16.517
- Well, maybe he is the Ripper.
I don't know.

19:16.550 --> 19:19.542
But if he's a plagiarist,
the real Chesapeake Ripper is

19:19.590 --> 19:22.684
gonna make sure
everybody knows it.

19:22.720 --> 19:25.928
(Jack sighs.)

19:25.960 --> 19:28.451
(phone ringing)

19:41.480 --> 19:43.448
- Hello.

19:43.480 --> 19:45.846
- [Jack. Jack.]

19:45.880 --> 19:47.438
- Who is this?

19:47.480 --> 19:49.710
- [Jack, it's Miriam.]

19:49.750 --> 19:53.789
[I don't know where I am.
I can't see anything.]
- Miriam?

19:53.820 --> 19:56.709
- [I was so wrong.
I was so wrong.]

19:56.760 --> 20:00.628
- Miriam?
- [Please... Jack. Please.]

20:00.660 --> 20:02.651
(Signal cuts out.)

20:10.270 --> 20:13.239
- I'm hooked in
to every carrier database

20:13.280 --> 20:15.601
and telephone provider
in the United States.

20:15.640 --> 20:17.801
Nothing.
- Look again.

20:17.850 --> 20:20.478
- I did my agains.
And my again and again

20:20.520 --> 20:22.670
and agains. I can't find
any electronic trace

20:22.720 --> 20:25.609
of any call made to your home
at 2:46am.

20:25.650 --> 20:27.789
- I am telling you
that the phone rang.

20:27.820 --> 20:30.823
- Wake your wife up?
- I was alone.

20:30.860 --> 20:33.897
- Whoever made that call could
have made it from that little
box outside your house

20:33.930 --> 20:36.296
or a junction
