39:31.700 --> 39:33.793
- Perhaps not so good
a memory after all.

39:33.830 --> 39:37.789
I don't recall a patient
with that name, but
it sounds familiar.

39:37.840 --> 39:42.072
- He was recently found
murdered in his workshop.
We think he may be a victim

39:42.110 --> 39:43.873
of the Chesapeake Ripper.

39:43.910 --> 39:46.799
- That's why he sounds familiar.
It was all over the news.

39:46.850 --> 39:50.411
- He had two old scars
on his thigh.

39:50.450 --> 39:53.044
Pathology checked with the local
hospital. He had fallen

39:53.090 --> 39:57.015
out of a tree-blind five years
ago while bow hunting--
stuck an arrow

39:57.060 --> 39:59.449
through his leg.
The doctor of record was

39:59.490 --> 40:02.152
a resident surgeon, but you were
on duty in the ER that night.

40:02.200 --> 40:07.092
- I was?
- Your name was
on the admi55ions log.

40:07.130 --> 40:09.530
- Let me think.

40:09.570 --> 40:11.538
You'll have to forgive me.

40:11.570 --> 40:14.607
I saw so many people in the ER,
but not so many hunters.

40:14.640 --> 40:17.473
- It's been a long time
since the accident,

40:17.510 --> 40:20.877
but I thought you may remember
if anything was fishy
with the arrow wound.

40:20.910 --> 40:23.470
- If it's the gentleman
I'm thinking of,

40:23.520 --> 40:26.080
I vaguely remember
a fellow hunter bringing him in,

40:26.120 --> 40:28.111
but _I recall
very little else.

40:28.150 --> 40:31.586
- Figured it was
a long shot.

40:34.090 --> 40:37.457
- I did keep detailed journals
during those days.

40:37.500 --> 40:41.732
If you like, I can get them
for you. Maybe you'll find
something helpful.

40:41.770 --> 40:43.965
- That would be great--
if you don't mind.

40:44.000 --> 40:47.208
- Not at all. If you'll wait
here, I'll be right back.

40:50.540 --> 40:51.939
- Thank you.

42:05.620 --> 42:08.885
- She was a very brave
young woman.

